title: Graph Data Model: Outdated Project Links
body:
Some of the links in the *Graph Data Model* Section are dead or the project have been retired/changed.

Here are the specific project links that might have to be updated:
* AgentsGraph - The link points to a domain that is now up for sale. The domain is not pointing to the project anymore. I have found the GithubLink to the project [here](https://github.com/bitnine-oss/agensgraph). Not sure if this is the correct project.
* Apache Giraph - The project has been retired since September 2023 according to the project page.
* Facebook TAO - The links points to a Facebook Page that is not accessible anymore (at least I was not able to access it)
* GraphLab PowerGraph - The link point to Apple's Turi Create Framework, a framework to simplify the creation of custom machine learning models.
* Intel GraphBuilder - The links does not point to the project anymore. It redirects to [here](https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/developer/topic-technology/open/overview.html) (Intel's Open Project Page)
* MapGraph - The link is dead.
* Twitter FlockDB - The projects has been archived since 18th September 2021
* NodeXL - The project page does not exist anymore.

The state of these links is as of 19th December 2023, at 14:42

title: Added the Shapley framework
body:
Shapley is a Python library for evaluating binary classifiers in a machine learning ensemble.

The library consists of various methods to compute (approximate) the Shapley value of players (models) in weighted voting games (ensemble games). We covered widely know approximation methods from well known economics and computer science research papers. There are also functionalities to identify the heterogeneity of the player pool. In addition, the framework comes with a detailed documentation, 100% test coverage and illustrative toy examples.

title: Added PyTorch Geometric Temporal
body:
PyTorch Geometric Temporal is a temporal (dynamic) extension library for PyTorch Geometric.

The library consists of various dynamic and temporal geometric deep learning, embedding, and spatio-temporal regression methods from a variety of published research papers. In addition, it consists of an easy-to-use dataset loader and iterator for dynamic and temporal graphs, gpu-support. It also comes with a number of benchmark datasets with temporal and dynamic graphs (you can also create your own datasets).

title: Added Little Ball of Fur
body: Little Ball of Fur consists of methods that can sample from graph structured data. To put it simply it is a Swiss Army knife for graph sampling tasks. First, it includes a large variety of vertex, edge, and exploration sampling techniques. Second, it provides a unified application public interface which makes the application of sampling algorithms trivial for end-users. Implemented methods cover a wide range of networking (Networking, INFOCOM, SIGCOMM) and data mining (KDD, TKDD, ICDE) conferences, workshops, and pieces from prominent journals.

title: Added Karate Club an unsupervised machine learning for graphs
body: Karate Club consists of state-of-the-art methods to do unsupervised learning on graph structured data. To put it simply it is a Swiss Army knife for small-scale graph mining research. First, it provides network embedding techniques at the node and graph level. Second, it includes a variety of overlapping and non-overlapping community detection methods. Implemented methods cover a wide range of network science (NetSci, Complenet), data mining (ICDM, CIKM, KDD), artificial intelligence (AAAI, IJCAI) and machine learning (NeurIPS, ICML, ICLR) conferences, workshops, and pieces from prominent journals.

title: It is recommended to increase computing middleware linkis and data application development portal DataSphere Studio
body:
* [Linkis](https://github.com/WeBankFinTech/Linkis)  - helps easily connect to various back-end computation/storage engines(Spark, Python, TiDB...), exposes various interfaces(REST, JDBC, Java ...), with multi-tenancy, high performance, and resource control.

* [DataSphere Studio](https://github.com/WeBankFinTech/DataSphereStudio)  - DataSphereStudio is a one stop data application development& management portal, covering scenarios including data exchange, desensitization/cleansing, analysis/mining, quality measurement, visualization, and task scheduling.
